Title: The Dangers of Infoprefixation (or, More Thoughts on the Impending Death of Information Architecture)

Author: jwecker
Content: One thing the article didn't make real clear was that the new features are all standards compliant- in theory most other browsers will end up doing the same things (though IMO it would be nice if Mozilla stays ahead).  Here is where you can see the web-programming landscape will look like in the next several years: http://www.whatwg.org/
